    <statement><div><p>Two similar containers have heights of <m>{3}</m> cm and <m>{6}</m> cm respectively. If the smaller container holds <m>{295}</m> ml, what is the capacity of the larger container? <alert>Note:</alert> Write your answer correct to <alert>2</alert> decimal places.</p>
<p><fillin characters="5" name="ans1"/> ml</p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>Given the linear scale factor (L.S.F)= <m>\frac{{6}}{{3}}</m></p>
<p>Volume scale factor (V.S.F) = <m>(L.S.F)^3 = (\frac{{6}}{{3}})^3 = {8}</m></p>
<p>Given the capacity of the small container as <m>{295}</m> ml, then the capacity of larger container is given by;</p>
<p><m>\quad \quad \quad \quad \quad \quad  \frac{{216}}{{27}}= \frac{x}{{295}} \Rightarrow x = \frac{{295}\times {216}}{{27}} = {2360}={2360}</m> ml</p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>2360</m></p></answer>
